long_desc.thetext:
This is what a user has reported with Trojitá and Cyrus when a search results in an empty result:

>>> y40 UID SEARCH RETURN (ALL) CHARSET utf-8 OR SUBJECT nameserv FROM nameserv&#9229;&#9226;
<<< * ESEARCH (TAG "y40")&#9229;&#9226;
<<< y40 OK Completed (0 msgs in 0.000 secs)&#9229;&#9226;

However, https://tools.ietf.org/search/rfc4731#page-3 says:

   An extended UID SEARCH command MUST cause an ESEARCH response with
   the UID indicator present.

Here's how Dovecot output looks like:

>>> y737 UID SEARCH RETURN (ALL UPDATE) CHARSET utf-8 OR SUBJECT pwnage FROM pwnage&#9229;&#9226;
<<< * ESEARCH (TAG "y737") UID&#9229;&#9226;
<<< y737 OK Search completed (0.238 secs).&#9229;&#9226;

(Ignore the UPDATE bits, of course.)
